<item>
            <title>[AMQ-4729] mKahaDB master slave needs lock when filtered adapter locks are created on the fly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-4729</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;mKahaDB directory=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;../kahadb&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
   &amp;lt;filteredPersistenceAdapters&amp;gt;
      &amp;lt;!-- kahaDB per destinations --&amp;gt;
      &amp;lt;filteredKahaDB perDestination=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt; &amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;persistenceAdapter&amp;gt;
          &amp;lt;kahaDB journalMaxFileLength=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;32mb&quot;&lt;/span&gt; /&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;/persistenceAdapter&amp;gt;
      &amp;lt;/filteredKahaDB&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;/filteredPersistenceAdapters&amp;gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;problem:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Starting the slave with an &quot;empty&quot; database, i.e no queues results in the slave trying to start and ultimately failing as the address is in use. There&apos;s now lock. Pushing a message to TEST.FOO and then starting the database works OK. The slave comes up and locks and waits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. Now, adding a TEST.FOO1 to the master. The master now has the two queues, TEST.FOO and TEST.FOO1. Kill the master and let the slave take over. The slave only sees TEST.FOO. Not TEST.FOO1.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
